Error’s 

Rabbitmq not work message please go through below..

1. Check ls -la ~/.erlang.cookie
2. sudo chown rabbitmq:rabbitmq /var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie
3. sudo chmod 400 /var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie

Then run:
```
sudo rabbitmq-plugins enable rabbitmq_management
```
or switch to rabbitmq user:
```
sudo su - rabbitmq
rabbitmq-plugins enable rabbitmq_management
```
Verify plugin
```
rabbitmq-plugins list | grep management
```
Still getting issue means
```
Restart RabbitMQ
```
```
sudo systemctl restart rabbitmq-server
```
or if Docker:
```
docker restart <rabbitmq_container>
```
Check RabbitMQ Process
```
ps -ef | grep rabbit & rabbitmq-server
```
